The incredibly talented @kozkreation put in a remarkable effort to create custom badges for a recent Defender project. The SwitchPath cat-back system from @awetuningofficial offer two distinct tones in one package. This kit unleashes a signature soundtrack out of the Z06, whether the valves are open or closed, thanks to its specifically tuned straight-through mufflers and precision-engineered x-pipe. It’s aggressive with the valves closed, and viscous with them open–just how a high-revving flat-plane V8 should be. Well-collected and comfortable when cruising (like stock), a riot when ripping, all controlled via the factory controls. If you’re planning on high flow cats, proceed with confidence as we engineered our mufflers to be fully capable of controlling those harsh frequencies. There’s also no need for a post-install visit to your local dealer for a valve relearn. Once it’s on, you’re clear for takeoff. Not only does the SwitchPath feature tier 1 OEM-supplied valves, included in every kit is a set of machined aluminum brackets to accommodate the factory valve motors and their factory linkage, keeping them away from the hot exhaust prolonging the lifespan of the electronics. Further, these valves won’t rattle a year later after installation – others on the market will. Two machined aluminum heat shields bolt-on to the Z06’s bumper using factory mounting points allowing the exhaust to shine through the mesh while protecting the inside of the bumper. No exhaust wraps that will inevitably become waterlogged and cause damage to whatever lies underneath. This exhaust system sheds 15lbs off your car’s weight getting rid of that heavy factory system. Topped off with quad 4.5” double-walled slash-cut tips exclusively in diamond black that fill the Z06’s bumper perfectly without any need for additional filler. The SwitchPath system does not interfere with any factory emissions equipment, so it is 100% emissions friendly, and a lifetime warranty comes standard. 😎

The Bead Grip technology by @methodracewheels lets you deflate tires to lower pressures that would normally require bead-lock wheels. Lowering tire pressure is an effective way to increase the tire’s contact with the ground, giving you better traction on loose terrain. You also get a smoother ride by softening the tire.

We love Method Wheels for a clear and concise approach to the wheel industry and home run execution, all at a price that puts the value off the charts! 🙌

This is top-of-the-line sound deadening right here! 💪

"The purpose of any vehicle audio installation is to provide a premium listening experience with clear, crisp, and emphasized sound. The best way to achieve this is by including sound deadening as part of the installation process.
That way, you ensure the sound you want to hear in your vehicle stays within and that the noise pollution of the road stays out.
Traditional sound deadening options tend to fall short by not approaching sound from various angles. Some are foil based, but lack the density of our butyl rubber. Others use open cell acoustic foam which allows for moisture absorption which can lead to mold and mildew issues. Adhesives that don’t grip as strongly as ours can lead to install slips and gap formations. Our sheets are oversized so installations can be done cleaner with less seams and disruption in the sound waves."

Minimizes glare from the sun and headlights, improving visibility and reducing eye strain.

Enhances privacy by reducing the visibility into your vehicle, safeguarding personal belongings.

Guards against fading and discoloration of your car’s interior due to prolonged sun exposure.

Adds a sleek and stylish appearance to your vehicle while complementing its overall design.

Holds shattered glass together in case of an accident, providing an added layer of safety.

The center channel is primarily responsible for reproducing vocals and center-panned audio content. Adding a dedicated center speaker can significantly improve the clarity and precision of vocals, making it feel like the sound is coming from a specific point in the center of the car.

A center channel also contributes to creating a more realistic and expansive soundstage. It helps anchor the vocals and central sound elements, allowing for a better localization of instruments and vocals, making the listening experience more immersive. With a center channel, you can achieve a more accurate stereo image, ensuring that the sonic elements are precisely placed within the space. This contributes to a more realistic representation of the original recording and enhances the overall listening enjoyment.

Distributing the audio workload among multiple speakers, including a center channel, can help reduce distortion. By allowing each speaker to focus on a specific range of frequencies, you can achieve cleaner and more accurate sound reproduction.

In high-end car audio builds, where attention to detail and audio quality are paramount, a center channel can be an integral part of a sophisticated multi-channel audio setup. This is common in premium audio systems designed to replicate studio-grade sound quality within the confines of a car. 🔊

This Cummins is breathing easier now, not only because of the Monster-Ram and cold air intake but also knowing that pesky grid heater bolt isn't going to be a real day-ruiner. 👀

"The Monster-Ram improves airflow from the intercooler and flows 1008 cfm (77.01 lbs/min) compared to Stock's measly 432 cfm (33.00 lbs/min). It raises boost without increasing backpressure at the turbine which results in a more responsive and power efficient engine. Up to four 1/8 inch NPT ports are pre drilled to measure pressure, temperature, or flow. The top two NPT ports are positioned to allow for proper atomization directly into the center of the air mass. Accommodates stock mounting points including Temperature and Pressure sensors, wire harness, and dipstick tube.

Maximum power, performance, and efficiency are the ultimate goals. To make it all happen the engine has to breathe freely and without needless restrictions. Finding ways to pump your engine full of cooler, denser air has always been the key.

Our High-Ram intakes have always whipped the competition. Our new Monster-Ram flat-out destroys it. Monster ram is CNC ported to a full 4.0 inches and was designed utilizing the latest in electronic computational fluid-dynamic technology. Next it was tested on the flow bench and dyno, then finally proven in the real world where the rubber meets the road. The Monster-Ram is a beast that only Banks could have unleashed. A simple, direct-replacement casting, Monster-Ram is instant power, performance, and acceleration gratification."

- Four 1/8-inch NPT ports (Top ports targeted for optimal atomization of Straight-Shot water-methanol)
- Includes custom fuel line, 4 to 3.5-inch hump hose, and all necessary hardware
- Optimizes air pressure and distribution going into the intake manifold
- Raises boost without increasing turbine drive pressure
- Improves flow of oxygen-rich air into cylinders
- Accommodates stock mounting points
- Improves airflow from the intercooler
- 4-inch CNC machined inlet
- Outflows stock over 133%
- Quicker throttle response
